[SN]TITLE[SN]
Parliament roof climber Braydon Anderson jailed

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who climbed on the roof of Parliament and caused Â£5,500 of damage during an an eight-hour stand off with police has been sentenced to seven months in jail.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Braydon Anderson sparked a security alert when he appeared on the roof after a climate change rally on 7 March last year.
Anderson, 23, of Portland Place, Northampton, admitted criminal damage.
He had smashed windows with a gold-plated crown he broke off a column.
Security at Parliament was re-examined after the incident and Speaker John Bercow told MPs immediate remedial action was being taken to address security failings.
